---
import Layout from '../components/Layout.astro';

const title = 'About the data';
const description = 'Where the calling-code dataset comes from, how it is stored, and what limitations exist in the MVP.';
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <h1 style="margin: 22px 0 6px;">About the data</h1>
  <div class="card" style="margin-top: 14px;">
    <p class="small">
      Phase 1 is intentionally <strong>static-first</strong>: the calling code data lives as versioned JSON inside this repo.
      That keeps the site cheap and immune to per-request compute bills.
    </p>

    <h2>Whatâ€™s included (MVP)</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Country name + ISO2 code</li>
      <li>Country calling code (digits only)</li>
      <li>Trunk prefix (if commonly used)</li>
      <li>Example formats + simple notes</li>
      <li>Origin exit codes (IDD prefix) for legacy formatting</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Limitations</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>This is not a full libphonenumber replacement (yet).</li>
      <li>Some countries have nuanced rules (e.g., Italy fixed lines) that need special-casing.</li>
      <li>Some calling codes are shared (e.g., NANP +1). We model that but keep parsing simple in Phase 1.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Verification</h2>
    <p class="small">The repo includes a dataset validator script so changes are safe and deterministic.</p>
    <p><span class="kbd">npm run validate-data</span></p>
  </div>
</Layout>
